documentation.text:
@notice Register to vote
 The function is called by the voter himself in order to upload
 the blinded UUID to the contract to be signed. Marking the
 voter as register, giving him ability to vote in the voting
 period. The function can be executed only during the registration
 period by only eligible voters.
 @param _blindedUUID: The blinded value of the voters UUID.

addVoters(address[]).notice: Add voters The operator adds the eligible voters' addresses to the contract.

constructor.notice: Constructor Initialize a vote. All the parameters are immutable once set. The name of the vote must not be empty string. The array of choices must not be empty, or contain empty strings. The value of registration start timestamp must be lesser than the registration end timestamp. The value of voting start timestamp must be lesser than the voting end timestamp, but greater than or equal to the registration end time. Finally the operators public key values must not be zero.

register(uint256).notice: Register to vote The function is called by the voter himself in order to upload the blinded UUID to the contract to be signed. Marking the voter as register, giving him ability to vote in the voting period. The function can be executed only during the registration period by only eligible voters.

signBlindedUUID(address,uint256).notice: Set voter's signed blinded UUID The operator signs the blinded UUID of the voter offchain and uploads it to the contract using this function.

tallyVotes(uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Tally the votes The function tally the results after they have been verified as valid by the operator. Requires the time of execution to be past the voting end time. Can be called only once by the operator.

vote(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256,uin.notice: Vote The voter cast his vote using this function. It takes all the values required to compose a Ballot and cast it. The voters public key values must not be zero. Same goes for the UUID and the unblinded signed UUID. This function can be executed only during voting period.
